						               													<description>A mysterious real history &amp;#10;A civilized opera 2000 years ago &amp;#10;A magical industrial history &amp;#10;A fascinating history of struggle   &amp;#10;A group of people with special positions who are emerging, flourishing and finally extinct in the vast ocean of history &amp;#10;- The Song of Salt&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In distant oriental continent, there is a position to maintain the stability of the country, i.e. salt administrator. &amp;#10;What is salt administrator? &amp;#10;Long time ago, salt played an important role in the social economy. In that era and background, salt administrator, as the highest leader in the salt production process, was formally appointed by the court of Northern Song Dynasty, ranking sixth in political circle and in charge of a salt field.  &amp;#10;On the other hand, the salt manufacturing is always dependent on fate from ancient times to date. Regardless of raw material collection or obtaining salt by drying bittern, they all are dependent on the generous gifts of nature. Now, as the new salt administrators appointed by the court, you have to complete the salt manufacturing task assigned by the court in the shortest possible time. You will face challenges from both competitors and nature, every choice you made may change the fate of the salt field. You will experience this piece of magical history in this game and master this ancient technology, salt manufacturing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The most important thing is that you will meet constant new challenges, and you should maintain a calm judgment on using which way for salt manufacturing. After hard works, there will be a mysterious final test. &amp;#10;Today, you are about to take office. In the next years of cooking bittern from the sea, the new salt administrators, please bring yourselves back to the ancient ages, and please achieve your ideal with fair decisions and rational minds, so as taste the difficulty in the ancient salt manufacturing process.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
